		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.75]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Pryss&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Of course, these things change depending on where you are, but i'd like to see what people most commonly use in hunting situations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Between level 12-16, I run thus:<br><br>DD<br>DOT<br>ROOT<br>TASHAN/MESMERIZE<br>SLOW DOWN<br>CHARM<br>MEM BLUR<br>PET SPELL<br><br>I run this way becuase the first three slots are hotkeyed for me and i use the attacks and root most often in the middle of the battle... slow downs, tashans, charms... only at the beginning really.  I mem charm and mem blur if the pet dies or in case I really need the target to leave me alone while I recover.  Pet spell in case I feel it's better to summon up more assistance while the target is mezzed post-pet death.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>&lt;&lt; Pryss Valjurai &gt;&gt;</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >5 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
